{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbc855a43-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3515d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3515d"},"text":"§ 3515d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Expenses of Office of Inspector General; protective services; investigating non-payment of child support","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For expenses necessary for the Office of Inspector General in carrying out the provisions of the Inspector General Act of 1978, as amended, $33,849,000: ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That of such amount, necessary sums are available for providing protective services to the Secretary and investigating non-payment of child support cases for which non-payment is a Federal offense under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s228"},"text":"section 228 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", each of which activities is hereby authorized in this and subsequent fiscal years."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbc855a44-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/1/tII"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(1) [title II]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-12-21"},"text":"Dec. 21, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2763"},"text":"114 Stat. 2763","children":[],"tail":", 2763A–24.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbc855a45-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbc855a46-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbc855a47-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Inspector General Act of 1978, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1101"},"text":"92 Stat. 1101","children":[],"tail":", which was set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees, and was substantially repealed and restated in chapter 4 (§ 401 et seq.) of Title 5 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3(b), 7, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4206"},"text":"136 Stat. 4206","children":[],"tail":", 4361. For disposition of sections of the Act into chapter 4 of Title 5, see Disposition Table preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbc855a48-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is from the Department of Health and Human Services Appropriations Act, 2001.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
